## Why each design decision matters

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| `timestamps.filter()` → always `store.set()` | `filter` returns a **new** array; without `set`, the Map still holds the unpruned copy, inflating memory and skewing `Retry-After` |
| `req.ip` only (no raw `x-forwarded-for` fallback) | Reading the header directly bypasses `trust proxy` — a client behind a transparent proxy could send `X-Forwarded-For: 1.2.3.4` and steal another IP's quota |
| `cleanupInterval.unref()` | Without it, a test suite or CLI that creates a limiter will hang for up to 60 s waiting for the timer to fire |
| `X-RateLimit-Reset` = `timestamps[0] + windowMs` | In a sliding window there is no single "reset time" — reporting when the oldest slot expires is the most actionable information a client can act on |
| `Retry-After` = `timestamps[0] + windowMs - now` | This is the exact millisecond the first slot will open, not an approximation — `Math.ceil` ensures the client doesn't retry one millisecond early and get another 429 |

